U.K.’s Osborne Plans Northern Rock Sale, Financial Times Says

-- B y   L a n a n h   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-06-11T08:47:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-11/u-k-s-osborne-plans-northern-rock-sale-financial-times-says.html
U.K. Chancellor of the Exchequer
 George Osborne  has decided a sale of government-owned Northern
Rock Plc will be the best outcome for taxpayers, the Financial
Times reported, without citing its sources.  The U.K. government was advised on a potential sale by
Deutsche Bank AG and U.K. Financial Investments Ltd., the body
which manages the British government’s ownership of Northern
Rock, Sky News City Editor Mark Kleinman wrote in the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lananh Nguyen in  London  at 
 Lnguyen35@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dick Schumacher at 
 dschumacher@bloomberg.net . 